Stock symbol GWSO, yesterday I mentioned I would be posting this company today at 6:30am. Kevin Harrington from the show shark tank is just now announcing he is a part of this company and this stock and company should do very well. Not to mention will do huge things for the ocean and environment. Definitely a stock to look at. Stock won’t be this cheap for long.
@globalwarmingresolution 👍

node.text:
Actual footage and A Rare Sighting of a Glass Octopus Reveals its Nearly Transparent Membrane in Extraordinary Detail

On a 34-day expedition around the Phoenix Islands Archipelago, marine scientists from the Schmidt Ocean Institute captured exceptionally rare footage of the elusive glass octopus. With a speckled, iridescent membrane, the aquatic animal is almost entirely transparent—only its optic nerve, eyes, and digestive tract are visible to humans—and sightings like these are so infrequent that scientists previously resorted to studying the species only after pulling it from the stomachs of its predators.

Source: thisiscolossal.com
Video by: @schmidtocean
#sea #octopus

🎥 and story by @onebreathdiver :
“These two are best friends, the Octopus dropped by to visit his friend. The Pufferfish was finding his home was way too small and needed to look for something a little more spacious....the Octopus said follow me I know the perfect spot, I've measured it, you'll have plenty of room to move. The Pufferfish was thrilled, a spacious new home with ocean views & lived happily ever after... 😁”
#sea

node.text:
Double tap if you think this is a beautiful shell 😍 

There's a reason why sea turtle shells are coloured the way they are. Countershading camouflages the turtles from potential predators. When viewed from above, the turtle’s dark back blends in with the ocean depths. From below, the lighter ventral side blends in with the brighter sea surface. 

📸 @slards via @masterreefguides
📍 Lady Musgrave Island
